### Messaging API Requests
# This file contains HTTP requests for testing Messaging and Template endpoints.
# Use VS Code REST Client extension to run these requests.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@authToken = YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE
@templateId = 1
@campaignId = 1
@customerId = 1

### 1. Get Templates
GET {{baseUrl}}/messaging/templates
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 2. Create Template
POST {{baseUrl}}/messaging/templates
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Promotional SMS",
  "channel": "sms",
  "subject": null,
  "body": "Hello {{firstName}}, enjoy 10% off this week at {{businessName}}.",
  "isActive": true
}   

### 3. Update Template
PUT {{baseUrl}}/messaging/templates/{{templateId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Promotional Message",
  "channel": "multi",
  "subject": "Special Offer for {{firstName}}",
  "body": "Hi {{name}}, we have a special offer for you this week.",
  "isActive": true
}

### 4. Delete Template
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/messaging/templates/{{templateId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 5. Send Bulk Message (Using Template)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messaging/bulk-messages
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "recipientIds": [1, 2, 3],
  "templateId": {{templateId}},
  "channels": ["email", "sms"]
}

### 6. Send Bulk Message (Custom Body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messaging/bulk-messages
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "recipientIds": [1, 2],
  "subject": "Stock Arrival Notice",
  "body": "Hello {{name}}, your requested items are now available.",
  "channels": ["email"]
}

### 7. Send Individual Message (Using Template)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messaging/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "recipientId": {{customerId}},
  "templateId": {{templateId}},
  "channels": ["sms"]
}

### 8. Send Individual Message (Custom Body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messaging/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "recipientId": {{customerId}},
  "subject": "Order Update",
  "body": "Hi {{firstName}}, your order is ready for pickup.",
  "channels": ["email", "sms"]
}

### 9. Get Messages History (All)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messaging/messages?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 10. Get Messages History (Filter by Recipient)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messaging/messages?page=1&limit=10&recipientId={{customerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 11. Get Message Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/messaging/messages/{{campaignId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### Notes
# Available placeholders in message/template body and subject:
# - {{name}}
# - {{firstName}}
# - {{lastName}}
# - {{businessName}}
# - {{email}}
# - {{phone}}
#
# Implemented channels:
# - email
# - sms
#
# Current role access for messaging routes:
# - ceo
# - manager
